    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Casts that have been created from molds taken directly from an existing work. After-casts are therefore made using the indirect lost-wax process, or in some instances by sand casting. The term is normally applied to bronzes, but may be applied to other types of casts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
